---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

// Reference data (sourced from widely-accepted specialty-coffee guidance, e.g. SCA golden-cup ~1:18).
const methods = [
  { m: 'Espresso',            ratio: '1:2',      grind: 'Fine',          temp: '90–96°C', time: '25–32 s',   note: 'Pressure brewed; ~18 g in, ~36 g out.' },
  { m: 'Moka pot',            ratio: '~1:10',    grind: 'Fine–medium',   temp: 'Off boil', time: '4–5 min',   note: 'Stovetop; take off heat as it gurgles.' },
  { m: 'AeroPress',           ratio: '1:13–1:16',grind: 'Medium-fine',   temp: '80–90°C', time: '1–2 min',   note: 'Forgiving; lower temp softens acidity.' },
  { m: 'Pour-over (V60)',     ratio: '1:16',     grind: 'Medium-fine',   temp: '92–96°C', time: '2:30–3:30', note: 'Bloom 30 s, then pour in stages.' },
  { m: 'Chemex',             ratio: '1:16–1:17', grind: 'Medium-coarse', temp: '92–96°C', time: '3:30–4:30', note: 'Thick filter = clean, bright cup.' },
  { m: 'French press',        ratio: '1:15',     grind: 'Coarse',        temp: '93–96°C', time: '4 min',     note: 'Full immersion; press slowly.' },
  { m: 'South Indian filter', ratio: '~1:5 decoction', grind: 'Fine',    temp: '~95°C',   time: '15–20 min', note: 'Strong decoction, served with hot milk.' },
  { m: 'Cold brew (concentrate)', ratio: '1:8',  grind: 'Coarse',        temp: 'Room / cold', time: '12–18 h', note: 'Dilute 1:1 with water or milk to serve.' },
];
---
<Layout
  title="Coffee Calculators & Brewing Ratios — Global Coffee Board"
  description="Free coffee brew-ratio calculator and espresso dial-in tool, plus a clear coffee-to-water ratio chart for pour-over, French press, AeroPress, Chemex, moka pot, cold brew and South Indian filter coffee."
  active="brewing"
>
  <header class="hero" style="padding:70px 0 24px">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="eyebrow">Brew better coffee</div>
      <h1 style="font-size:clamp(2.2rem,5vw,3.6rem)">Coffee <span class="grad">calculators</span> &amp; brewing ratios</h1>
      <p class="lead">Dial in any brew method with the right coffee-to-water ratio. Use the calculators below, then keep the ratio chart handy for pour-over, French press, espresso and more.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main>
    <!-- CALCULATORS -->
    <section class="section" id="calculators" style="padding-top:16px">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="section-head reveal">
          <div class="eyebrow">Coffee Calculators</div>
          <h2>Get the measurements right</h2>
          <p>Weighing beats scooping. Enter your numbers and brew with confidence.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="calc-tabs reveal" role="tablist">
          <button type="button" class="calc-tab active" data-tab="percup">Coffee Per Cup</button>
          <button type="button" class="calc-tab" data-tab="ratio">Coffee to Water Ratio</button>
          <button type="button" class="calc-tab" data-tab="espresso">Espresso Dial-in</button>
        </div>

        <!-- 1) Coffee Per Cup -->
        <div class="calc-panel active" data-panel="percup">
        <div class="calc-title">
          <span class="calc-badge">1</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Coffee Per Cup Calculator</h3>
            <p>How much ground coffee for the number of cups you want to brew.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="rc glass">
          <div class="rc-grid">
            <div class="rc-inputs">
              <div class="rc-block">
                <div class="rc-eyebrow">How many cups?</div>
                <input id="pc-cups" class="rc-amount" type="number" inputmode="numeric" min="1" value="2" />
              </div>
              <div class="rc-block">
                <div class="rc-eyebrow">Cup size</div>
                <div class="chip-row" id="pc-size">
                  <button type="button" class="chip" data-ml="177">Small · 6 oz</button>
                  <button type="button" class="chip active" data-ml="237">Cup · 8 oz</button>
                  <button type="button" class="chip" data-ml="355">Mug · 12 oz</button>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="rc-block">
                <div class="rc-eyebrow">Strength</div>
                <div class="chip-row" id="pc-strength">
                  <button type="button" class="chip" data-ratio="18">Mild 1:18</button>
                  <button type="button" class="chip active" data-ratio="16">Medium 1:16</button>
                  <button type="button" class="chip" data-ratio="14">Strong 1:14</button>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="rc-recipe">
              <div class="rc-recipe-head">Your recipe</div>
              <div class="rc-big" id="pc-out">29.6</div>
              <div class="rc-big-unit">grams of coffee</div>
              <div class="rc-tiles">
                <div class="rc-tile"><b id="pc-tbsp">5.9</b><span>tablespoons</span></div>
                <div class="rc-tile"><b id="pc-scoop">3.0</b><span>scoops</span></div>
                <div class="rc-tile"><b id="pc-water">474</b><span>ml water</span></div>
              </div>
              <div class="rc-strength-label" id="pc-strength-label">Medium</div>
              <div class="rc-mug">
                <svg class="rc-mug-svg" viewBox="0 0 108 90" aria-hidden="true">
                  <clipPath id="pc-mugclip"><rect x="14" y="12" width="56" height="66" rx="8"/></clipPath>
                  <rect id="pc-mug-fill" x="14" y="46" width="56" height="32" fill="var(--caramel)" clip-path="url(#pc-mugclip)"/>
                  <rect x="14" y="12" width="56" height="66" rx="8" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="4"/>
                  <path d="M70 28 h12 a11 11 0 0 1 0 32 h-12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="4"/>
                </svg>
                <span id="pc-note">2 cups · 8 oz each</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="rc-summary-head">Recipe summary</div>
          <div class="rc-summary" id="pc-summary">For 2 cups (8 oz each) at medium strength, use 29.6 g of coffee (about 5.9 tablespoons) and 474 ml of water.</div>
          <div class="rc-actions">
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" id="pc-copy">Copy recipe</button>
            <button type="button" class="btn" id="pc-reset">Reset</button>
          </div>
        </div>

        </div>

        <!-- 2) Coffee to Water Ratio -->
        <div class="calc-panel" data-panel="ratio">
        <div class="calc-title">
          <span class="calc-badge">2</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Coffee to Water Ratio Calculator</h3>
            <p>Dial in any ratio and get the exact dose — grams, tablespoons or scoops.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- Coffee-to-water ratio calculator -->
        <div class="rc glass">
          <div class="rc-grid">
            <!-- LEFT: inputs -->
            <div class="rc-inputs">
              <div class="rc-block">
                <div class="rc-eyebrow">What do you want to find?</div>
                <div class="chip-row" id="rc-mode">
                  <button type="button" class="chip active" data-mode="coffee">How much coffee</button>
                  <button type="button" class="chip" data-mode="water">How much water</button>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="rc-block">
                <div class="rc-eyebrow" id="rc-amount-label">Water amount</div>
                <input id="rc-amount" class="rc-amount" type="number" inputmode="decimal" min="0" value="500" />
                <div class="chip-row" id="rc-unit">
                  <button type="button" class="chip active" data-unit="grams">grams</button>
                  <button type="button" class="chip" data-unit="ml">ml</button>
                  <button type="button" class="chip" data-unit="oz">oz</button>
                  <button type="button" class="chip" data-unit="cups">cups</button>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="rc-block">
                <div class="rc-eyebrow rc-ratio-head"><span>Ratio strength</span><span class="rc-ratio-val" id="rc-ratio-val">1:16</span></div>
                <div class="rc-lead">1 part coffee to <b id="rc-ratio-den">16</b> parts water</div>
                <input id="rc-ratio" class="rc-range" type="range" min="8" max="20" step="1" value="16" />
                <div class="rc-scale"><span>1:8 strong</span><span>1:16 balanced</span><span>1:20 light</span></div>
                <div class="chip-row rc-presets" id="rc-presets">
                  <button type="button" class="chip" data-ratio="16">Drip 1:16</button>
                  <button type="button" class="chip" data-ratio="17">Pour Over 1:17</button>
                  <button type="button" class="chip" data-ratio="15">French Press 1:15</button>
                  <button type="button" class="chip" data-ratio="8">Cold Brew 1:8</button>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- RIGHT: recipe -->
            <div class="rc-recipe">
              <div class="rc-recipe-head">Your recipe</div>
              <div class="rc-big" id="rc-out">31.3</div>
              <div class="rc-big-unit" id="rc-out-unit">grams of coffee</div>
              <div class="rc-tiles">
                <div class="rc-tile"><b id="rc-tbsp">6.3</b><span>tablespoons</span></div>
                <div class="rc-tile"><b id="rc-scoop">3.1</b><span>scoops</span></div>
                <div class="rc-tile"><b id="rc-counter">500</b><span id="rc-counter-label">g water</span></div>
              </div>
              <div class="rc-strength">
                <div class="rc-strength-bar"><span class="rc-strength-dot" id="rc-strength-dot"></span></div>
                <div class="rc-strength-scale"><span>Bold</span><span>Balanced</span><span>Light</span></div>
              </div>
              <div class="rc-strength-label" id="rc-strength-label">Balanced</div>
              <div class="rc-mug">
                <svg class="rc-mug-svg" viewBox="0 0 108 90" aria-hidden="true">
                  <clipPath id="rc-mugclip"><rect x="14" y="12" width="56" height="66" rx="8"/></clipPath>
                  <rect id="rc-mug-fill" x="14" y="46" width="56" height="32" fill="var(--caramel)" clip-path="url(#rc-mugclip)"/>
                  <rect x="14" y="12" width="56" height="66" rx="8" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="4"/>
                  <path d="M70 28 h12 a11 11 0 0 1 0 32 h-12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="4"/>
                </svg>
                <span id="rc-batch">about a large batch</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="rc-summary-head">Recipe summary</div>
          <div class="rc-summary" id="rc-summary">For 500 g of water at a 1:16 ratio, use 31.3 g of coffee, about 6.3 tablespoons or 3.1 scoops.</div>
          <div class="rc-actions">
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" id="rc-copy">Copy recipe</button>
            <button type="button" class="btn" id="rc-reset">Reset</button>
          </div>
        </div>

        </div>

        <!-- 3) Espresso dial-in -->
        <div class="calc-panel" data-panel="espresso">
        <div class="calc-title">
          <span class="calc-badge">3</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Espresso dial-in</h3>
            <p>Check your dose-to-yield ratio for a balanced shot.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="rc rc-espresso glass">
          <div class="rc-grid">
            <div class="rc-inputs">
              <div class="rc-block">
                <div class="rc-eyebrow">The shot</div>
                <p class="rc-lead" style="margin:0 0 4px">Enter your dose and shot yield to see the brew ratio.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="rc-block">
                <div class="rc-eyebrow">Dose in — dry grounds (g)</div>
                <input id="es-dose" class="rc-amount" type="number" inputmode="decimal" step="0.1" min="0" value="18" />
              </div>
              <div class="rc-block">
                <div class="rc-eyebrow">Yield out — liquid espresso (g)</div>
                <input id="es-yield" class="rc-amount" type="number" inputmode="decimal" step="0.1" min="0" value="36" />
              </div>
              <p style="color:var(--text-dim);font-size:.8rem;margin:0">Tip: aim for a ~25–32 s shot. Too fast → grind finer; too slow → grind coarser.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rc-recipe">
              <div class="rc-recipe-head">Your shot</div>
              <div class="rc-big" id="es-ratio">1 : 2.00</div>
              <div class="rc-big-unit">brew ratio</div>
              <div class="rc-strength">
                <div class="rc-strength-bar"><span class="rc-strength-dot" id="es-dot"></span></div>
                <div class="rc-strength-scale"><span>Ristretto</span><span>Espresso</span><span>Lungo</span></div>
              </div>
              <div class="rc-strength-label" id="es-verdict">Balanced espresso</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- BREWING & RATIOS -->
    <section class="section" id="ratios" style="padding-top:0">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="section-head reveal">
          <div class="eyebrow">Brewing &amp; Ratios</div>
          <h2>The ratio chart</h2>
          <p>A quick reference for coffee-to-water ratio, grind, water temperature and brew time by method.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="glass reveal" style="padding:8px">
          <div class="table-wrap">
            <table class="data">
              <thead><tr><th>Method</th><th>Ratio</th><th>Grind</th><th>Water temp</th><th>Time</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                {methods.map((r) => (
                  <tr>
                    <td><b>{r.m}</b></td><td>{r.ratio}</td><td>{r.grind}</td><td>{r.temp}</td><td>{r.time}</td>
                    <td style="color:var(--text-muted)">{r.note}</td>
                  </tr>
                ))}
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="article" style="margin-top:34px">
          <div class="callout"><b>The golden ratio.</b> A widely used starting point is roughly <b>1 gram of coffee to 16–18 grams of water</b> (the Specialty Coffee Association's "golden cup" sits near 55 g of coffee per litre). Go lower (1:15) for a bolder cup, higher (1:17–1:18) for a lighter, tea-like brew.</div>
          <h2>How to use ratios</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><b>Weigh, don't scoop.</b> Beans vary in density, so a scale (0.1 g for espresso, 1 g for filter) is the single biggest upgrade to consistency.</li>
            <li><b>Grind to the method.</b> Finer for faster/pressurised brews (espresso, moka), coarser for long immersions (French press, cold brew).</li>
            <li><b>Mind the water.</b> Just off the boil (92–96°C) for most filter methods; cooler (80–90°C) tames acidity in an AeroPress.</li>
            <li><b>Adjust one thing at a time.</b> Bitter or harsh? Coarsen the grind or shorten the brew. Sour or thin? Grind finer or brew a touch longer.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Fragment slot="scripts">
    <script is:inline src="/assets/js/brewing.js"></script>
  </Fragment>
</Layout>
